<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Grandma's Recipe Collection - Traditional Family Recipes</title>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Grandma's Secret Recipe Collection</h1>
        <p><em>Passed down through generations</em></p>
    </header>

    <nav>
        <h2>Recipe Categories</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#appetizers">Appetizers</a></li>
            <li><a href="#main-dishes">Main Dishes</a></li>
            <li><a href="#desserts">Desserts</a></li>
            <li><a href="#beverages">Beverages</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <main>
        <section id="main-dishes">
            <h2>Main Dishes</h2>
            
            <article>
                <h3>Classic Chicken Biryani</h3>
                <p><strong>Prep Time:</strong> 30 minutes | <strong>Cook Time:</strong> 45 minutes</p>
                <p><em>Serves 6 people</em></p>

                <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>2 cups Basmati rice</li>
                    <li>1 kg chicken, cut into pieces</li>
                    <li>2 large onions, sliced</li>
                    <li>1 cup yogurt</li>
                    <li>2 tbsp ginger-garlic paste</li>
                    <li>Biryani spices (bay leaves, cardamom, cinnamon)</li>
                    <li>Salt to taste</li>
                    <li>Oil for cooking</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>Instructions:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Soak rice in water for <strong>30 minutes</strong></li>
                    <li>Marinate chicken with yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, and spices</li>
                    <li>Fry onions until <em>golden brown</em></li>
                    <li>Cook marinated chicken until tender</li>
                    <li>Boil rice with whole spices until 70% cooked</li>
                    <li>Layer rice and chicken alternately</li>
                    <li>Cook on low heat for 45 minutes</li>
                    <li>Serve hot with raita and salad</li>
                </ol>

                <blockquote>
                    <p>"The secret ingredient is always love and patience." - Grandma</p>
                </blockquote>
            </article>
        </section>

        <section id="desserts">
            <h2>Traditional Desserts</h2>
            
            <article>
                <h3>Homemade Chocolate Cake</h3>
                <p><small>A family favorite for over 50 years!</small></p>
                
                <h4>Dry Ingredients:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
                    <li>1 cup cocoa powder</li>
                    <li>2 cups sugar</li>
                    <li>1 tsp baking soda</li>
                    <li>1/2 tsp salt</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>Wet Ingredients:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>1 cup milk</li>
                    <li>1/2 cup vegetable oil</li>
                    <li>2 large eggs</li>
                    <li>1 tsp vanilla extract</li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>Baking Time:</strong> 30-35 minutes at 350¬∞F</p>
                <p><em>Perfect for birthdays and special occasions!</em></p>
            </article>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>These recipes have been in our family for generations.</p>
        <p><strong>Happy Cooking!</strong> üë®‚Äçüç≥</p>
