<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>The Solar System - Science Project by Sarah Smith</title>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Exploring Our Solar System</h1>
        <p><strong>Science Project</strong> by <em>Sarah Smith</em></p>
        <p><small>Grade 8 - Room 205</small></p>
    </header>

    <nav>
        <h2>Project Contents</h2>
        <ol>
            <li><a href="#introduction">Introduction</a></li>
            <li><a href="#planets">The Eight Planets</a></li>
            <li><a href="#facts">Amazing Facts</a></li>
            <li><a href="#conclusion">Conclusion</a></li>
        </ol>
    </nav>

    <main>
        <section id="introduction">
            <h2>Introduction to Our Solar System</h2>
            <p>Our solar system consists of the <strong>Sun</strong> and everything that orbits around it, including planets, moons, asteroids, and comets.</p>
            <p>It formed approximately <em>4.6 billion years ago</em> from a giant molecular cloud.</p>
            
            <blockquote>
                <p>"The universe is not only stranger than we imagine, it is stranger than we can imagine." - J.B.S. Haldane</p>
            </blockquote>
        </section>

        <section id="planets">
            <h2>The Eight Planets</h2>
            
            <article>
                <h3>Inner Planets (Rocky Planets)</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Mercury</strong> - Closest to the Sun</li>
                    <li><strong>Venus</strong> - Hottest planet</li>
                    <li><strong>Earth</strong> - Our home planet</li>
                    <li><strong>Mars</strong> - The Red Planet</li>
                </ol>
                
                <p><em>These planets are made mostly of rock and metal.</em></p>
            </article>

            <article>
                <h3>Outer Planets (Gas Giants)</h3>
                <ol start="5">
                    <li><strong>Jupiter</strong> - Largest planet</li>
                    <li><strong>Saturn</strong> - Has beautiful rings</li>
                    <li><strong>Uranus</strong> - Tilted on its side</li>
                    <li><strong>Neptune</strong> - Windiest planet</li>
                </ol>
                
                <p><em>These planets are made mostly of gas and ice.</em></p>
            </article>
        </section>

        <section id="facts">
            <h2>Amazing Solar System Facts</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>The Sun contains <strong>99.86%</strong> of the system's mass</li>
                <li>Jupiter has more than <em>75 moons</em></li>
                <li>A day on Venus is longer than its year</li>
                <li>Saturn would <small>float in water</small> if there was a bathtub big enough</li>
                <li>Mars has the largest volcano in the solar system</li>
                <li>Neptune takes <strong>165 Earth years</strong> to orbit the Sun once</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Temperature Extremes</h3>
            <p>Mercury can reach <strong>800¬∞F (427¬∞C)</strong> during the day but drop to <strong>-300¬∞F (-184¬∞C)</strong> at night!</p>
        </section>

        <section id="conclusion">
            <h2>Project Conclusion</h2>
            <p>Our solar system is an <em>incredible</em> place filled with diverse worlds and fascinating phenomena.</p>
            <p>Each planet has its own unique characteristics that make it special.</p>
            <p><strong>Future exploration</strong> will help us learn even more about our cosmic neighborhood.</p>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p><small>Sources: NASA, National Geographic, Encyclopedia Britannica</small></p>
        <p>Project completed on: <strong>March 15, 2024</strong></p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>

